@title Welcome to the documentation of the Ceylan-LEEC API

@doc <h3>Overview</h3>

<p>The `Ceylan-LEEC' library (a fork of <a href="https://github.com/gbour/letsencrypt-erlang" target="_blank">letsencrypt-erlang</a>) allows to interact from Erlang/OTP with servers implementing the <b>ACME protocol</b> - specifically Let's Encrypt servers, mostly in order to generate <b>X.509 certificates</b>.
</p>

<p>This website presents the documentation of the API (<em>Application Programming Interface</em>) of LEEC version PROJECT_VERSION (as of GENERATION_DATE).
</p>


<p>Ceylan-LEEC relies on the <a href="http://myriad.esperide.org" target="_blank">Myriad layer</a>, a generic Erlang toolbox.
</p>


@reference See the <a href="http://leec.esperide.org" target="_blank">LEEC official</a> or <a href="https://olivier-boudeville.github.io/Ceylan-LEEC/index.html" target="_blank">its mirror</a>

